---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'En el Fertil Suelo';
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="En el Fertil Suelo — Work"
  description="En el Fertil Suelo (2017–2018). Video, sculpture. X Premio Luis Caballero. Inspired by Homer's Iliad. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 008</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2017–2018 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Video, sculpture &nbsp;/&nbsp; X Premio Luis Caballero</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: En el Fertil Suelo — Video still, two figures meeting ]</div>
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: En el Fertil Suelo — Sculptural element, installation view ]</div>
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: En el Fertil Suelo — Installation view at Galeria Santa Fe ]</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            Inspired by Homer's <em>Iliad</em> — the passage where Achaeans and Trojans,
            after ten years of war, decide to lay down their arms — the work presents two
            characters who have found each other to move forward. The piece draws a parallel
            between the ancient epic and Colombia's contemporary moment, exploring the
            possibility of encounter after prolonged conflict.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The title, <em>En el Fertil Suelo</em> (In the Fertile Soil), evokes the
            potential for renewal that lies in the aftermath of destruction — a ground
            made fertile not despite but because of what has transpired upon it. Through
            video and sculpture, Escallon constructs a space where reconciliation is not
            a conclusion but a gesture, tentative and ongoing.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The work was created during Colombia's post-peace accord period, following the
            2016 agreement between the government and the FARC. This historical context
            gives the Homeric reference a particular urgency — the question of whether
            enemies can truly lay down their arms resonates beyond literary allusion into
            the lived reality of a society attempting to imagine itself after war.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">CONTEXT</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            <em>En el Fertil Suelo</em> was presented as part of the X Premio Luis Caballero,
            one of Colombia's most prestigious art prizes. The work continues Escallon's
            long engagement with the consequences of violence and the material and symbolic
            traces left by conflict — themes present in earlier works such as <em>Desde
            Adentro</em> and <em>En Estado de Coma</em>.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The peace accord signed in 2016 between the Colombian government and the FARC
            guerrilla marked a turning point in over fifty years of armed conflict. Escallon's
            response avoids direct political commentary, instead offering a poetic meditation
            on the possibility — and difficulty — of encounter between those who have been
            adversaries.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>En el Fertil Suelo</strong><br>
            2017–2018<br><br>
            Video, sculpture.<br><br>
            Variable dimensions
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">AWARDS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            X Premio Luis Caballero<br>
            Galeria Santa Fe, Bogota, 2017–2018
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">EXHIBITIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            X Premio Luis Caballero — Galeria Santa Fe, 2017–2018
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2017–2018). <em>En el Fertil Suelo</em>.
            Video, sculpture. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/en-el-fertil-suelo/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    }
</style>
